    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of September 10 Private Sector column about choice of Russell Crowe to play leading role in film about John Forbes Nash Jr, which misstated screenwriter Akiva Goldsman's name (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>A brief report in the Private Sector column last Sunday about the choice of Russell Crowe to play the leading role in a film about John Forbes Nash Jr., the 1994 Nobel laureate in economic science, misstated the surname of the screenplay writer. He is Akiva Goldsman, not Goldman.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>A brief report in the Private Sector column last Sunday about the choice of Russell Crowe to play the leading role in a film about John Forbes Nash Jr., the 1994 Nobel laureate in economic science, misstated the surname of the screenplay writer. He is Akiva Goldsman, not Goldman.</p>
      </block>
